          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The target   materials   consisted  of  0.21  -  0.30",
                " mg/cm**2 thin films of Th-232 - O-2,  U-nat.  - O-3,",
                " and  93  %  enriched  U-235 - O-2 oxides prepared om",
                " mica sheets as supports and were contacted with  100",
                " micron thick Makrofol N,  Bayer AG,  which served as",
                " detectors   for   fission   fragments.   The   total",
                " effective  numbers  of  target  nuclei for different",
                " stacks were 3.4, 8.1, and 1.9 units of 10**18 cm**-2",
                " for Th-232, U-238, and U-235, respectively."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EXTB",
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TRD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " 100  micron thick Macrofol N,  Bayer AG,  foils",
                " and mica foils."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The direct fission fragment track counting."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "To obtain the final values of the physical quantities",
                " and associated errors, the data have been treated by",
                " considering the geometry  of  exposure,  statistics,",
                " counting    and   registration   efficiencies,   and",
                " fission-track background."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Experimental fissility   data    from    photofission",
                " reactions of Th-232,  U-238,  and U-235 muclei at 52",
                " MeV have been obtained using monochromatic and fully",
                " polarized  photon beams and dielectric fission-track",
                " detectors.  These data,  along with literature  data",
                " for Np-237,  U-235,238,  Th-232, Bi-209, Pb-208, and",
                " Yb-174  nuclei  have  been   analyzed   within   the",
                " framework   of   a   simple   two-step   model   for",
                " photofission  reactions,  i.e.,  absorption  of  the",
                " incident  photon by a neutron - proton pair followed",
                " by an evaporation-fission competition mechanism  for",
                " excited  nucleus.  For  nuclei in the ta - np region",
                " the trend of calculated  fissilities  clearly  shows",
                " shell effects in the vicinity of Pb-208. In the case",
                " of  U-238  the  effect  of  photon  polarization  on",
                " fission   direction   has  also  been  studied,  and",
                " isotropy was  observed  in  the  fragment  azimuthal",
                " distribution."
              ]
            }
          ],
